# Salesforce Platform Basics

Salesforce is a cloud-based platform used to build business applications, manage customer data, automate workflows, and improve business operations. It provides tools for creating apps, storing records, generating reports, and managing users through an easy web interface.

The Salesforce Platform works on cloud computing technology, which means users can access applications and data from anywhere using the internet. It is widely used for Customer Relationship Management (CRM), sales management, service management, and custom application development.

Salesforce supports both:
- Configuration (click-based development)
- Coding (programming-based development)

The platform includes important components such as:
- Apps
- Objects
- Tabs
- Fields
- Records
- Reports
- Dashboards

Businesses use Salesforce because it is secure, scalable, easy to maintain, and supports automation.

---

# 1️⃣ What is Salesforce Platform?

Salesforce Platform is a cloud-based platform used to develop and manage business applications. It helps organizations store customer information, automate processes, create reports, and improve productivity without installing software locally.

